               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17860426-47-person713">
                  CHARLES
                   COOPER
               <interp inst="t17860426-47-person713" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860426-47-person713" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860426-47-person713" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>The prisoner came into the shop the 3d of April, about three in the afternoon to buy some silk; she fixed on three colours, and I went to the other end of the counter to weigh it; I observed a motion of her hand to that part of the counter where this silk was; she bought fourpenny worth, and went away; I missed the wrapper, and went after, and brought her into the shop, and I just perceived her drop the wrapper from under her coats; I knew the wrapper, being pieced in several places.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I am thirteen years old; I did not meddle with it.</p>
               <p>The prisoner's mother appeared for her character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17860426-47-verdict238" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17860426-47-verdict238" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
